A vintage 1970s technical illustration style image showing a complex maze of interconnected postal tubes and pneumatic delivery systems in warm sepia and burnt orange tones. At the center, a single sealed capsule containing a rolled document travels through transparent glass tubes that branch and merge like a subway map. The tubes wind through an intricate mechanical framework of brass gears, valves, and routing switches. Small destination markers dot junction points along the pathways. The composition has a cross-section view revealing the inner workings, reminiscent of vintage encyclopedia cutaway diagrams with subtle paper texture and aged printing effects.
